I tend to feel very deeply, and I have many different ways of processing each of these feelings - though often processing my feelings involves sharing my feelings with others. If I am joyful or in awe, I find that my experience of these feelings are validated when I share them with others. When I am feeling anger or frustration, I find I need to talk through these feelings with the person/situation I am feeling angry with in order to let go/move on from those feelings. 

I feel most known when people verbally express a desire to understand me. This manifests as deep conversations in which I have the opportunity to ask and answer big, and often personal, questions. I measure much of my self worth in my ability to show others love.
